\begin_layout Standard
The concept or property of symmetry can be observed in a variety of contexts:
 in an image, a construction, etc.
 In this thesis we will restrict the domain of symmetry to automatic reasoning.
 If you could identify the symmetries of a problem, one could use that informati
on to reduce the difficulty analizing in detail only one of these simmetric
 cases and generalitazing after.
 This is exactly what we try to do when we use the simmetries of a problem
 in automatic reasoning.
 The presence of simmetries in subspaces that do not contain any solutions
 can be used by our algorithm, guiding it to search for solutions somewhere
 else.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In particular, we will focus on detecting simmetries in description logics.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First, we will elaborate the theorical basis for the main concepts and explain
 how these concepts are related to each other.
 We will create a sintactic and semantic bridge between description logics
 and modal logic, basing it on the work from 
